name: reseller
title: Enterprise Apps Reseller API
description: Creates and manages your customers and their subscriptions.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies the resource as a subscription change plan request. Value: subscriptions#seats

fields.name: licensedNumberOfSeats
fields.desc: Read-only field containing the current number of licensed seats for FLEXIBLE Google-Apps subscriptions and secondary subscriptions such as Google-Vault and Drive-storage.

fields.name: maximumNumberOfSeats
fields.desc:
The maximumNumberOfSeats property is the maximum number of licenses that the customer can purchase. This property applies to plans other than the annual commitment plan. How a user's licenses are managed depends on the subscription's payment plan:  
- annual commitment plan (with monthly or yearly payments) — For this plan, a reseller is invoiced on the number of user licenses in the numberOfSeats property. The maximumNumberOfSeats property is a read-only property in the API's response.  
- flexible plan — For this plan, a reseller is invoiced on the actual number of users which is capped by the maximumNumberOfSeats. This is the maximum number of user licenses a customer has for user license provisioning. This quantity can be increased up to the maximum limit defined in the reseller's contract. And the minimum quantity is the current number of users in the customer account.  
- 30-day free trial plan — A subscription in a 30-day free trial is restricted to maximum 10 seats.

fields.name: numberOfSeats
fields.desc:
The numberOfSeats property holds the customer's number of user licenses. How a user's licenses are managed depends on the subscription's plan:  
- annual commitment plan (with monthly or yearly pay) — For this plan, a reseller is invoiced on the number of user licenses in the numberOfSeats property. This is the maximum number of user licenses that a reseller's customer can create. The reseller can add more licenses, but once set, the numberOfSeats can not be reduced until renewal. The reseller is invoiced based on the numberOfSeats value regardless of how many of these user licenses are provisioned users.  
- flexible plan — For this plan, a reseller is invoiced on the actual number of users which is capped by the maximumNumberOfSeats. The numberOfSeats property is not used in the request or response for flexible plan customers.  
- 30-day free trial plan — The numberOfSeats property is not used in the request or response for an account in a 30-day trial.

fields.name: dealCode
fields.desc: Google-issued code (100 char max) for discounted pricing on subscription plans. Deal code must be included in insert requests in order to receive discounted rate. This property is optional, regular pricing applies if left empty.

fields.name: renewalSettings
fields.desc: Renewal settings for the annual commitment plan. For more detailed information, see renewal options in the administrator help center.

fields.name: suspensionReasons
fields.desc:
Read-only field containing an enumerable of all the current suspension reasons for a subscription. It is possible for a subscription to have many concurrent, overlapping suspension reasons. A subscription's STATUS is SUSPENDED until all pending suspensions are removed.

Possible options include:  
- PENDING_TOS_ACCEPTANCE - The customer has not logged in and accepted the G Suite Resold Terms of Services.  
- RENEWAL_WITH_TYPE_CANCEL - The customer's commitment ended and their service was cancelled at the end of their term.  
- RESELLER_INITIATED - A manual suspension invoked by a Reseller.  
- TRIAL_ENDED - The customer's trial expired without a plan selected.  
- OTHER - The customer is suspended for an internal Google reason (e.g. abuse or otherwise).

fields.name: trialSettings
fields.desc: The G Suite annual commitment and flexible payment plans can be in a 30-day free trial. For more information, see the API concepts.

fields.name: isInTrial
fields.desc:
Determines if a subscription's plan is in a 30-day free trial or not:
- true — The plan is in trial.
- false — The plan is not in trial.

fields.name: trialEndTime
fields.desc: Date when the trial ends. The value is in milliseconds using the UNIX Epoch format. See an example Epoch converter.

fields.name: billingMethod
fields.desc: Read-only field that returns the current billing method for a subscription.

fields.name: creationTime
fields.desc: The creationTime property is the date when subscription was created. It is in milliseconds using the Epoch format. See an example Epoch converter.

fields.name: plan
fields.desc: The plan property is required. In this version of the API, the G Suite plans are the flexible plan, annual commitment plan, and the 30-day free trial plan. For more information about the API"s payment plans, see the API concepts.

fields.name: isCommitmentPlan
fields.desc:
The isCommitmentPlan property's boolean value identifies the plan as an annual commitment plan:
- true — The subscription's plan is an annual commitment plan.
- false — The plan is not an annual commitment plan.

fields.name: planName
fields.desc:
The planName property is required. This is the name of the subscription's plan. For more information about the Google payment plans, see the API concepts.

Possible values are:  
- ANNUAL_MONTHLY_PAY — The annual commitment plan with monthly payments  
- ANNUAL_YEARLY_PAY — The annual commitment plan with yearly payments  
- FLEXIBLE — The flexible plan  
- TRIAL — The 30-day free trial plan. A subscription in trial will be suspended after the 30th free day if no payment plan is assigned. Calling changePlan will assign a payment plan to a trial but will not activate the plan. A trial will automatically begin its assigned payment plan after its 30th free day or immediately after calling startPaidService.

fields.name: commitmentInterval
fields.desc: In this version of the API, annual commitment plan's interval is one year.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: An annual commitment plan's interval's endTime in milliseconds using the UNIX Epoch format. See an example Epoch converter.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: An annual commitment plan's interval's startTime in milliseconds using UNIX Epoch format. See an example Epoch converter.

fields.name: purchaseOrderId
fields.desc: This is an optional property. This purchase order (PO) information is for resellers to use for their company tracking usage. If a purchaseOrderId value is given it appears in the API responses and shows up in the invoice. The property accepts up to 80 plain text characters.

fields.name: skuId
fields.desc: A required property. The skuId is a unique system identifier for a product's SKU assigned to a customer in the subscription. For products and SKUs available in this version of the API, see  Product and SKU IDs.

fields.name: skuName
fields.desc: Read-only external display name for a product's SKU assigned to a customer in the subscription. SKU names are subject to change at Google's discretion. For products and SKUs available in this version of the API, see  Product and SKU IDs.

fields.name: customerId
fields.desc: This property will always be returned in a response as the unique identifier generated by Google. In a request, this property can be either the primary domain or the unique identifier generated by Google.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies the resource as a Subscription. Value: reseller#subscription

fields.name: subscriptionId
fields.desc: The subscriptionId is the subscription identifier and is unique for each customer. This is a required property. Since a subscriptionId changes when a subscription is updated, we recommend not using this ID as a key for persistent data. Use the subscriptionId as described in retrieve all reseller subscriptions.

fields.name: resourceUiUrl
fields.desc: URL to customer's Subscriptions page in the Admin console. The read-only URL is generated by the API service. This is used if your client application requires the customer to complete a task using the Subscriptions page in the Admin console.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: This is an optional property.

fields.name: transferInfo
fields.desc: Read-only transfer related information for the subscription. For more information, see retrieve transferable subscriptions for a customer.

fields.name: minimumTransferableSeats
fields.desc: When inserting a subscription, this is the minimum number of seats listed in the transfer order for this product. For example, if the customer has 20 users, the reseller cannot place a transfer order of 15 seats. The minimum is 20 seats.

fields.name: transferabilityExpirationTime
fields.desc: The time when transfer token or intent to transfer will expire. The time is in milliseconds using UNIX Epoch format.

fields.name: customerDomain
fields.desc: Primary domain name of the customer

fields.name: seats
fields.desc: This is a required property. The number and limit of user seat licenses in the plan.

schemas.name: ChangePlanRequest
schemas.desc: JSON template for the ChangePlan rpc request.

fields.name: dealCode
fields.desc: Google-issued code (100 char max) for discounted pricing on subscription plans. Deal code must be included in changePlan request in order to receive discounted rate. This property is optional. If a deal code has already been added to a subscription, this property may be left empty and the existing discounted rate will still apply (if not empty, only provide the deal code that is already present on the subscription). If a deal code has never been added to a subscription and this property is left blank, regular pricing will apply.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies the resource as a subscription change plan request. Value: subscriptions#changePlanRequest

fields.name: planName
fields.desc:
The planName property is required. This is the name of the subscription's payment plan. For more information about the Google payment plans, see API concepts.

Possible values are:  
- ANNUAL_MONTHLY_PAY - The annual commitment plan with monthly payments  
- ANNUAL_YEARLY_PAY - The annual commitment plan with yearly payments  
- FLEXIBLE - The flexible plan  
- TRIAL - The 30-day free trial plan

fields.name: purchaseOrderId
fields.desc: This is an optional property. This purchase order (PO) information is for resellers to use for their company tracking usage. If a purchaseOrderId value is given it appears in the API responses and shows up in the invoice. The property accepts up to 80 plain text characters.

fields.name: seats
fields.desc: This is a required property. The seats property is the number of user seat licenses.

schemas.name: Address
schemas.desc: JSON template for address of a customer.

fields.name: addressLine3
fields.desc: Line 3 of the address.

fields.name: countryCode
fields.desc: For countryCode information, see the ISO 3166 country code elements. Verify that country is approved for resale of Google products. This property is required when creating a new customer.

fields.name: locality
fields.desc: An example of a locality value is the city of San Francisco.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: An example of a region value is CA for the state of California.

fields.name: addressLine1
fields.desc: A customer's physical address. An address can be composed of one to three lines. The addressline2 and addressLine3 are optional.

fields.name: addressLine2
fields.desc: Line 2 of the address.

fields.name: contactName
fields.desc: The customer contact's name. This is required.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies the resource as a customer address. Value: customers#address

fields.name: organizationName
fields.desc: The company or company division name. This is required.

fields.name: postalCode
fields.desc: A postalCode example is a postal zip code such as 94043. This property is required when creating a new customer.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies the resource as a customer. Value: reseller#customer

fields.name: phoneNumber
fields.desc: Customer contact phone number. This can be continuous numbers, with spaces, etc. But it must be a real phone number and not, for example, "123". See phone  local format conventions.

fields.name: postalAddress
fields.desc: A customer's address information. Each field has a limit of 255 charcters.

fields.name: resourceUiUrl
fields.desc: URL to customer's Admin console dashboard. The read-only URL is generated by the API service. This is used if your client application requires the customer to complete a task in the Admin console.

fields.name: alternateEmail
fields.desc: Like the "Customer email" in the reseller tools, this email is the secondary contact used if something happens to the customer's service such as service outage or a security issue. This property is required when creating a new customer and should not use the same domain as customerDomain.

fields.name: customerDomain
fields.desc: The customer's primary domain name string. customerDomain is required when creating a new customer. Do not include the www prefix in the domain when adding a customer.

fields.name: customerDomainVerified
fields.desc: Whether the customer's primary domain has been verified.

fields.name: customerId
fields.desc: This property will always be returned in a response as the unique identifier generated by Google. In a request, this property can be either the primary domain or the unique identifier generated by Google.

optinalQueryParams.name: customerNamePrefix
optinalQueryParams.desc:
When retrieving all of your subscriptions and filtering for specific customers, you can enter a prefix for a customer name. Using an example customer group that includes exam.com, example20.com and example.com:  
- exa -- Returns all customer names that start with 'exa' which could include exam.com, example20.com, and example.com. A name prefix is similar to using a regular expression's asterisk, exa*. 
- example -- Returns example20.com and example.com.

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: When retrieving a large list, the maxResults is the maximum number of results per page. The nextPageToken value takes you to the next page. The default is 20.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken

requiredQueryParams.name: deletionType
requiredQueryParams.desc: The deletionType query string enables the cancellation, downgrade, or suspension of a subscription.

enum.name: cancel
enum.desc: Cancels the subscription immediately. This does not apply to a G Suite subscription.

enum.name: downgrade
enum.desc:
Downgrades a G Suite subscription to a Google Apps Free edition subscription only if the customer was initially subscribed to a Google Apps Free edition (also known as the Standard edition). Once downgraded, the customer no longer has access to the previous G Suite subscription and is no longer managed by the reseller.

A G Suite subscription's downgrade cannot be invoked if an active or suspended Google Drive or Google Vault subscription is present. The Google Drive or Google Vault subscription must be cancelled before the G Suite subscription's downgrade is invoked.

The downgrade deletionType does not apply to other products or G Suite SKUs.

enum.name: suspend
enum.desc:
(DEPRECATED) The G Suite account is suspended for four days and then cancelled. Once suspended, an administrator has access to the suspended account, but the account users can not access their services. A suspension can be lifted, using the reseller tools.

A G Suite subscription's suspension can not be invoked if an active or suspended Google Drive or Google Vault subscription is present. The Google Drive or Google Vault subscription must be cancelled before the G Suite subscription's suspension is invoked.

enum.name: transfer_to_direct
enum.desc: Transfers a subscription directly to Google.  The customer is immediately transferred to a direct billing relationship with Google and is given a short amount of time with no service interruption. The customer can then choose to set up billing directly with Google by using a credit card, or they can transfer to another reseller.
